Lawyer Evans Monari when he represented Maj Gen(rtd) Hussein Ali at ICC. [Courtesy]  Evans Monari, one of the lawyers in President Uhuru's legal team at ICC is dead.  Family spokesman Ken Monari said the late died on Monday night at the Nairobi Hospital’s Intensive Care Unit after a long illness.  Monari is said to have battling multiple complications of his internal organs.  The deceased is an advocate of the High Court of Kenya and was a Partner in Coulson Harney, Advocates where he was the Head of Dispute Resolution and Arbitration.  New CBC teacher will allow pupils to take the lead in learning process  ICC rejects Gicheru request to suspend hearing tomorrow over ‘unfair’ judge  Why lawyer Paul Gicheru wants ICC judge Samba disqualified from case  Gicheru’s trial at ICC set for March 2022 Monari is among lawyer that handled high profile criminal briefs.  He represented former Police Commissioner Hussein Ali who faced Crimes Against Humanity Charges in The Hague-based International Criminal Court (ICC) arising from the 2007-08 post-election violence in Kenya.  He has been the co-vice chair of the International Bar Association Africa Forum, representing the Law Society on the Board of the Council for Law Reporting.      Karim Khan achukua kiapo cha afisi ya ICC, ana kibarua kikubwa kinachomsubiri  New ICC Boss: British human rights lawyer Karim Khan elected as new ICC prosecutor  Sonko aachiliwa kwa dhamana ya shillingi laki tatu kwenye kesi kumi za kuwajeruhi watu na wizi By Stephen Rutto | 20 minutes ago By Moses Nyamori | 1 hour ago By Martin Ndiema | 2 hours ago By Yvonne Chepkwony | 8 hours ago